Error Code: E102

Problem
Motor Overheating

Description
Error E102 occurs when the spindle motor temperature exceeds the safe operating limit.

Possible Causes

• Cooling fan failure
• Coolant blockage
• Continuous operation for more than 6 hours
• Bearing damage
• High ambient temperature

Repair Steps

1. Switch OFF the machine.
2. Disconnect the power supply.
3. Remove the motor cover.
4. Inspect the cooling fan.
5. Clean the coolant filter.
6. Check motor bearings.
7. Replace damaged fan if necessary.
8. Restart the machine.

Safety Checklist

✔ Disconnect electrical power.
✔ Wear insulated gloves.
✔ Allow motor to cool for 15 minutes.
✔ Lock-Out Tag-Out (LOTO).
✔ Verify emergency stop is active.

Required Tools

Allen Key Set
Torque Wrench
Multimeter
Coolant Filter
Cleaning Brush

Estimated Repair Time

20 Minutes

Preventive Maintenance

• Clean coolant filter every week.
• Inspect cooling fan monthly.
• Lubricate bearings every 3 months.
• Record maintenance in maintenance log.

